Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.72,0:04:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:276720,279765}Who the hell are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.76,0:04:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:279765,283352}I don't think they're your\Nregular bandits looking for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.35,0:04:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:283352,286438}It looked like a provocation\Nagainst our government.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.23,0:04:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:287231,289066}A provocation?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.06,0:04:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:289066,293862}In other words, this whole Count Red\Nis a supporter of the Paris occupiers?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.57,0:04:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:294571,296990}In my opinion,\Nit is the only sensible option.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.61,0:05:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:297616,300035}Panza, and what do you\Nthink about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.36,0:05:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:300369,302871}I agree with this gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.00,0:05:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:316009,320430}In that case, they also obviously know\Nthat we want to sign a secret agreement
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.43,0:05:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:320430,324434}with the Prussian army and that\Nwe will try to sell Paris to them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.64,0:05:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:324643,326770}This is a serious problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.77,0:05:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:326770,330315}If Count Red steals the document\Nthat Prussia is about to send to us
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.31,0:05:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:330315,335862}and make it public, we won't be\Nsafe anywhere in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.24,0:05:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:338240,343161}This document cannot see\Nthe daylight, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.16,0:05:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:343161,345289}I am fully aware of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.28,0:05:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:345289,347332}Panza, look out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.79,0:05:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:351795,353839}Count Red's minions!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.83,0:05:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:353839,355257}Panza, don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.25,0:05:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:355257,356383}But why, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.46,0:06:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:357467,360679}Now he will go to inform his leaders\Nabout our agreement with Prussia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.13,0:06:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:362139,366435}You're so thick at times.\NHe's our pawn now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.43,0:06:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:366435,367352}Our pawn?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.85,0:06:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:367853,373025}We'll smoke them out. The document\Nis just a bait that will let us find them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.02,0:06:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:373025,375944}You will receive\Nthe real document, Panza.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.94,0:06:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:375944,379031}We cannot afford another failure\Nlike the one in London, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.03,0:06:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:379031,382784}Yes sir! I swear on my life\Nthat I will not let you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.78,0:06:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:382784,384286}By the way, Mr. Thiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.28,0:06:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:384286,388874}How did it happen that we let Isabelle return\Nto Versailles, as if nothing had happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.75,0:06:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:389750,392169}It's Captain Langlois' wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.58,0:06:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:392586,394254}Captain Langlois'?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.50,0:06:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:394504,397841}He's popular with his subordinates\Nand easy to manipulate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.84,0:06:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:397841,401928}It's good to have some ace\Nup your sleeve.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.22,0:06:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:403221,406058}We'll use him\Nuntil he's worn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.65,0:07:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:418653,421490}Isabelle, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.49,0:07:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:421490,427579}{\fscx95}Do you have any idea how much your ridiculous\Nbehavior hurt the Rostains' reputation?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.20,0:07:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:428205,434127}Father, I went to London\Nnot for our family, let alone for Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.12,0:07:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:434127,437506}I did it just to help my sister—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.50,0:07:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:437506,441218}Silence, Isabelle!\NI will not let you talk back to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.13,0:07:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:444137,448725}Ah, Victor. Do you think\Nthat I raised my children badly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.72,0:07:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:448725,453563}Why is it that my children don't care at all\Nabout what is happening at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.10,0:07:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:454106,460153}I do not know. I abandoned money\Nfor a military career myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.15,0:07:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:460153,462531}I'm not the one that can\Nanswer your question.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.53,0:07:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:462531,466952}Victor. The Rostains are a venerable family\Nthat dates back three hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.49,0:07:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:467494,471248}I could not bear the thought\Nthat our lineage would be forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.24,0:07:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:471248,473542}I just want to\Nprotect our heritage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.54,0:07:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:473542,474334}Darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.00,0:08:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:476002,480465}Both Isabelle and Geneviève are proud\Nwomen, perfectly worth our family's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.46,0:08:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:480465,483802}Their actions are simply caused\Nby the times we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.80,0:08:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:490809,493437}The times we live in…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.97,0:08:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:493979,495355}Mr. Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.64,0:08:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:495647,498650}A messenger from\NMr. Thiers came to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.10,0:08:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:499109,500777}What? From Thiers?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.82,0:08:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:502821,507367}Captain Langlois, you are ordered\Nto appear at the palace immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.62,0:08:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:518628,519963}Count Red?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.96,0:08:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:519963,525093}Yes. You are the only one\Nable to capture this criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.09,0:08:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:525093,528889}As far as I know, their group\Nis just a bunch of bandits.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.88,0:08:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:528889,532350}Shouldn't the police handle this?\NTo involve the army…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.35,0:08:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:532350,534686}Count Red is an enemy\Nof our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.68,0:08:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:534686,538106}Are you going to argue\Nwith my orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.56,0:09:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:538565,540358}No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.77,0:09:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:540775,543111}Here is my order,\NCaptain Langlois.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.11,0:09:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:543111,546239}Destroy the shadow army\Nled by Count Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.23,0:09:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:546239,549034}Understood? I have already\Nmade some preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:562088,564883}{\i1}Victor against Count Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.88,0:09:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:564883,567802}{\i1}And so, these two men,\Nwho saved Isabelle in London,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.80,0:09:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:567802,571181}{\i1}were put at the ends\Nof their swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.21,0:10:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:649217,651261}Where have you been, Irma?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.26,0:10:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:651261,653346}I know, I know, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.34,0:10:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:653346,656349}I keep telling you\Nnot to risk unnecessarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.34,0:11:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:656349,660103}I want to be useful to you.\NBesides, we're both in this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.10,0:11:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:660103,662063}Together?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.60,0:11:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:663607,669237}All these weapons and jewels are to be\Nused to defend Paris and its people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.65,0:11:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:669654,671489}That's why…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.48,0:11:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:671489,673199}That's hardly a justification.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.61,0:11:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:674618,677787}"You are a woman.\NThe role of a woman lies elsewhere."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.78,0:11:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:677787,679914}I don't want to\Nlisten to this rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.50,0:11:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:682500,684836}Better tell me\Nwhat you think about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:684836,687839}Soon Prussia will secretly send some\Nimportant document to Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.83,0:11:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:687839,689591}What are you talking about?\NAre you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.43,0:11:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:699434,702646}{\i1}Neither Count Red\Nnor anyone from his shadow army
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.64,0:11:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:702646,707275}{\i1}could even guess that it was\Nyet another of Thiers' traps.
Comment: 0,0:12:16.76,0:12:16.76,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:736763,736763}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.54,0:12:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:770547,771715}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.75,0:12:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:773758,776886}Please remain calm.\NWe are not interested in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.88,0:12:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:776886,779556}All we're asking you\Nis to hand over that parcel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.11,0:13:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:795113,796239}Bloody hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.32,0:13:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:800326,802203}Count Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.20,0:13:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:802203,803955}Resistance is futile.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.58,0:13:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:804581,806666}{\i1}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.16,0:13:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:807167,809377}You fell into our ambush.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.37,0:13:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:809377,812213}I do not like this method,\Nbut that was the order I was given.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.21,0:13:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:812213,814591}If you do not resist,\Nwe will spare you life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.88,0:13:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:818887,821347}Did I say anything funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.35,0:13:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:825351,826936}Look what I got here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.73,0:13:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:834736,836196}Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.82,0:14:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:841826,843244}– Irma!\N– My love!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.00,0:14:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:849000,850460}After them. After them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.27,0:14:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:874275,877111}{\i1}Not good. Behind these trees\Nthere's the Rostains' estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.50,0:15:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:899509,903763}Be good and nobody will get hurt.\NBelieve it or not, but we don't like killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.97,0:15:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:910979,913982}{\i1}As I thought,\Nthey took them hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.28,0:15:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:921281,925952}{\i1}Who would've thought that of all places,\Nwe're going to fight here. Life is so ironic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.03,0:15:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:927036,929205}{\i1}Father. Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.62,0:15:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:931624,934210}Apparently,\Ntheir daughter is upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.21,0:15:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:934210,936129}I'll go check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.33,0:15:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:937338,939382}Just don't hurt her, Irma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.04,0:15:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:940049,942176}That depends on\Nwhat she will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.50,0:16:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:980506,981966}Stay calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.84,0:16:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:983843,986554}Don't struggle and I won't\Ndo anything to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.55,0:16:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:986554,987388}Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.38,0:16:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:987388,989307}One of the\NCount Red's shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.51,0:16:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:990516,993019}It's… Is that you, Isabelle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.36,0:16:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004364,1005949}Enough of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.36,0:16:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1009369,1011079}Words out of my mouth,\Nmy friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.24,0:16:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1013247,1015375}Isabelle, cover yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.56,0:17:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1040566,1042068}{\i1}This fighting style…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.94,0:17:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1045947,1047949}{\i1}You're good, Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.62,0:17:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1053621,1055623}That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.96,0:17:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1061963,1064257}Count Red… You are…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.84,0:17:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1066843,1072056}How about you remove your mask?\NCount Red, or rather… Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.93,0:17:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1072932,1076602}You saw through me, Victor.\NI can't say I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.60,0:18:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1076602,1080023}Your fighting style gave you away.\NI could never forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.02,0:18:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1080023,1082692}I'm glad you're alive, Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.73,0:18:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1083735,1085653}Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.52,0:18:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1086529,1088781}What… What just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.11,0:18:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1093119,1095872}I'm sorry you had to worry\Nbecause of me, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.66,0:18:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1096664,1099250}Andréa… Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.25,0:18:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1099250,1100084}Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.05,0:18:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1108051,1114390}{\i1}Yes. Count Red was to die\Nin the Battle of Champigny.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.39,0:18:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1114390,1119729}{\fscx95\i1}It was Andréa whom Thiers was supposed to put\Nto death in a battle with no chance of winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.36,0:18:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1132366,1134786}{\i1}After the Battle of\NChampigny was over,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.78,0:18:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1134786,1138414}{\i1}Andréa started wandering\Naimlessly on the verge of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.41,0:19:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1138414,1142752}{\i1}He was saved by a group\Nof Gypsies who were passing by.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.64,0:19:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1155640,1159727}{\i1}Under the tender care of Irma,\None of the gypsy girls,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.72,0:19:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1159727,1164690}{\i1}Andréa pulled through and\Neventually jumped back on his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.98,0:19:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1171989,1179080}{\i1}Irma taught Andréa many things: sadness\Nand the hardships associated with poverty,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.08,0:19:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1179080,1183084}{\i1}but also the simple joy of life\Nand how to appreciate each day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.58,0:19:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1186587,1195513}{\i1}It was a life that Andréa,\Nborn to a wealthy family, never knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.51,0:20:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1195513,1202103}{\i1}Andréa saw for the first time\Nwhat he really wanted to protect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.41,0:20:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1218411,1227503}{\i1}Spending day after day with each other,\NIrma and Andréa got very close.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.50,0:20:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1231507,1233634}{\i1}My love…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.80,0:20:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1234802,1236637}{\i1}Irma.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.16,0:21:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1260161,1262872}Good job, Irma!\NThe girl has a taste!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.71,0:21:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1270713,1273758}{\i1}I can't sit here\Ndoing nothing forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.46,0:21:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1275468,1278012}{\i1}Somebody help me…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.18,0:21:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1288189,1294904}{\i1}Andréa understood\Nwhat he should be fighting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.03,0:21:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1303037,1307416}All my brothers in arms\Nwho survived the Battle of Champigny
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.41,0:21:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1307416,1309794}pledged to take\Nrevenge on Thiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.79,0:21:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1309794,1315591}By taking revenge on him, we will\Nsave the oppressed citizens of Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.59,0:21:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1315591,1318302}Over time, more and more\Npeople joined us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.30,0:22:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1318302,1323349}Soon we formed an army of shadows\Nand I became Count Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.18,0:22:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1324183,1327561}You do realize, however,\Nthat you are breaking French law?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.43,0:22:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1328437,1333442}Laws made by villains from Versailles such as\NThiers don't amount to a spit in the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.44,0:22:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1333442,1336821}We respect the laws\Nof people who protect Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.82,0:22:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1336821,1340658}What would you say, Victor,\Nif I suggested you to join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.20,0:22:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1342201,1344787}I am a soldier of the\NVersailles government.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.78,0:22:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1344787,1348874}Whatever the government,\Nas a soldier, I must obey its orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.95,0:22:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1349959,1352753}You haven't changed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.80,0:22:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1358801,1359760}What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.80,0:22:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1360803,1361846}What's going on there?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.84,0:22:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1361846,1363889}Trouble, boss! It's the army!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.88,0:22:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1363889,1367226}The French army surrounded\Nthe mansion and they're shooting at us!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.72,0:22:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1367727,1371147}The French troops? But why?\NWhy are they attacking the Rostains' estate?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.81,0:22:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1371814,1373816}What's going on in Thiers' head?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.81,0:22:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1373816,1377111}Victor, now you can see\Nwhat a rat he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.62,0:23:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1386620,1390541}The Rostain family\Ngives shelter to Count Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.54,0:23:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1390541,1393419}This is treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.41,0:23:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1393419,1397089}Their property is hereby confiscated\Nby the government of Versailles!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.21,0:23:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1398215,1402887}Count Red. Inadvertently,\Nyou have done us a huge favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.88,0:23:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1402887,1406766}Thanks to you,\Nthe Rostains' assets will be ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.11,0:23:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1418110,1421405}{\i1}Crumbling walls and pillars.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.90,0:23:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1421906,1427578}{\i1}Isabelle, seeing the sudden collapse\Nof the Rostain family, forgot everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.57,0:23:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1427578,1431332}{\i1}She just stood speechless and looked\Nat the hell raging around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.70,0:23:56.75,Credits,[credits],0,0,0,,{TIME:1431707,1436754}{\fad(200,200)\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.7\fs17\an5\pos(515,364)\t(2972,4972,5,\c&H101010&)}To be continued
Comment: 0,0:23:57.42,0:23:57.42,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:1437421,1437421}Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.42,0:24:00.38,Default,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:1437421,1440382}Next episode preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.92,0:24:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1441926,1445471}Thiers' attack sweeps away\Nmy family's mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.47,0:24:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1445471,1448140}Mom loses her life\Ncrushed by a chandelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.14,0:24:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1448140,1453020}Moments later, our father follows her.\NNothing makes any sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.02,0:24:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1453020,1460152}My brother, Victor and I barely escape.\NTogether with Jean, we decide to go to Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.15,0:24:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1460152,1462696}Next time on "Isabelle from Paris":
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.69,0:24:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1462696,1467326}"I Hate The War That Killed Mother".\NPlease look forward to it.
Comment: 0,0:24:27.32,0:24:27.32,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:1467326,1467326}Ending
